# BROWSER-publish.md - Substack Newsletter Publishing Patterns

## SS 8. Create & Publish Newsletter Post

### Step 1 — Navigate to editor

Navigate directly to `{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/post` — creates a new draft immediately.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://{{handle}}.substack.com/publish/post"}' 2>&1
```

🚨 **Do NOT use "Create" button on dashboard** — it does not reliably open the post editor.
🚨 **Do NOT use "New post" nav button** — it opens the Notes composer, NOT the article editor.

### Step 2 — Fill title and subtitle

Title and subtitle use `<textarea>`, NOT contenteditable.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var titleTA = document.querySelector('textarea[placeholder=\"Title\"]'); var subtitleTA = document.querySelector('textarea[placeholder*=\"subtitle\"]'); if (titleTA) { titleTA.focus(); titleTA.value = window.__data.title; titleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); titleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); } if (subtitleTA) { subtitleTA.focus(); subtitleTA.value = window.__data.subtitle; subtitleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); subtitleTA.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); } return { titleSet: !!titleTA, subtitleSet: !!subtitleTA }; }", "data": {"title": "YOUR_TITLE", "subtitle": "YOUR_SUBTITLE"}}
ENDJSON
```

### Step 3 — Write body content

🚨 **Body uses `div[contenteditable="true"]` (ProseMirror/TipTap editor).** First one on page is the body editor.
🚨 **Clear first** (editor may have default subscribe/thanks blocks).
🚨 **Paste as HTML** — the editor accepts rich HTML and renders it correctly.

**Supported HTML formatting (verified 2026-03-28):**
- `<h2>` — section headings
- `<strong>` — bold
- `<em>` — italic
- `<a href="...">` — links (including Substack profile links like `https://substack.com/@handle`)
- `<ul><li>` — bullet lists
- `<blockquote><p>` — blockquotes
- `<p>` — paragraphs

🚨 **@mentions via HTML paste do NOT work** — the `substack-mention` span bleeds content. Reference writers via `<a href="https://substack.com/@handle">Name</a>` links instead.
🚨 **Hashtags are NOT supported** in the newsletter editor (Notes only).

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var editor = document.querySelectorAll('div[contenteditable=\"true\"]')[0]; if (!editor) return { error: 'no editor' }; editor.focus(); document.execCommand('selectAll'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); document.execCommand('delete'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var html = window.__data.html; var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/html', html); dt.setData('text/plain', 'fallback'); editor.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); if (editor.innerText.length < 100) { document.execCommand('insertText', false, html); } return { typed: true, len: editor.innerText.length }; }", "data": {"html": "<p>YOUR_ARTICLE_HTML</p>"}}
ENDJSON
```

### Step 4 — Wait for auto-save

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var saved = btns.find(b => /saved/i.test(b.innerText.trim())); return { saved: saved ? saved.innerText.trim() : 'not found' }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

### Step 5 — Open publish settings, configure audience, add tag

Click "Continue" to open publish panel. Set audience + comments to "everyone". Add at least 1 tag (required for publish).

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var continueBtn = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Continue'; }); if (!continueBtn) return { error: 'no Continue button' }; continueBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var radios = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('input[type=\"radio\"]')); var audienceEveryone = radios.find(function(r) { return r.name === 'audience' && r.value === 'everyone'; }); if (audienceEveryone && !audienceEveryone.checked) { audienceEveryone.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); } var commentEveryone = radios.find(function(r) { return r.name === 'commentLevel' && r.value === 'everyone'; }); if (commentEveryone && !commentEveryone.checked) { commentEveryone.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); } var tagInput = document.querySelector('input[placeholder=\"Select or create tags\"]'); if (tagInput) { tagInput.focus(); tagInput.value = window.__data.tag; tagInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); var options = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[role=\"option\"]')); var createOpt = options.find(function(o) { return o.innerText.includes('Create'); }); if (createOpt) { createOpt.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); } } return { settingsOpen: true }; }", "data": {"tag": "YOUR_TAG"}}
ENDJSON
```

Replace `TAG_PLACEHOLDER` with a topic tag (e.g. "fitness", "productivity"). At least 1 tag is required for publish.

### Step 6 — Publish

Substack shows up to 2 confirmation dialogs after clicking Publish. Handle all in sequence.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var publishBtn = btns.find(function(b) { var t = b.innerText.trim(); return t === 'Send to everyone now' || t === 'Publish now'; }); if (!publishBtn) return { error: 'no publish button' }; publishBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var subscribeDialog = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Publish without buttons'; }); if (subscribeDialog) { subscribeDialog.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); } var sendEmail = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Also send via email'; }); if (sendEmail) { sendEmail.click(); return { published: true, method: 'email' }; } var webOnly = btns.find(function(b) { return b.innerText.trim() === 'Publish on web only'; }); if (webOnly) { webOnly.click(); return { published: true, method: 'web_only' }; } return { published: true, method: 'direct' }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

After publish, page navigates to share-center. `Execution context was destroyed` or `Inspected target navigated` is NORMAL.

### Step 7 — Verify published

Wait 3s for navigation, then check:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var isLive = document.body.innerText.includes('Your post is live'); var url = window.location.href; return { published: isLive || url.includes('share-center'), url: url }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

Success indicators:
- URL contains `/share-center`
- Page text contains "Your post is live!"
- Post appears on `{{handle}}.substack.com`

